msContents.summary: Devotional book containing prayers, questions and answers about religious practice, protective devices and other devotional materials.

author.name: Free Library of Philadelphia. Rare Book Department. John Frederick Lewis Collection of Oriental Manuscripts

supportDesc.extent: 83 leaves : 116 x 85 (90 x 70), bound to 117 x 95 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Unfoliated; catchwords every verso, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a West African naskh in three different hands; black ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: A few simple line and dot decorations in black ink.

binding.p: Reddish leather over pasteboard with flap (Type II); shadows from a central mandorla, cornerpieces and border onlays remain; hinge and flap doublure is painted with purple and green geometric pattern, otherwise plain paper doublure.

origin.p: The item is undated; probably produced in the 19th or early 20th century.

history.provenance: Acquired with the Pepper Fund in January 1926 (note in pencil, f. [83]v).
